AU  - Kitchens, Brent
AU  - Parham, Robert
AU  - Yung, Chris
T1  - Is news really news? The effects of selective disclosure regulations
PY  - 2024
Y1  - 2024/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfae030
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 28
IS  - 6
SP  - 1991
EP  - 2015
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Before regulations were enacted to prevent such practices, information leaked through selective disclosure was incorporated into markets prior to the public release of news. “News days” did not deliver news to markets; now they do. We provide novel evidence of changes in returns and turnover behavior around the enactment of regulations barring selective disclosure practices in the United States and the EU. We conversely document lack of such changes in Australia and Japan, which did not implement similar measures. We conclude that selective disclosure resolves Roll’s R2 puzzle.
Y2  - 4/28/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfae030
ER  - 




